rComments: Really great professor that didn't make an easy class "hard for nothing". Really, he cares for your success, asks for participation (he loves his participation marks), and will always be there to answer your questions. His classes are not heavy and are interesting, which makes learning fun.

Even though the course material is difficult, he will adapt his teaching and take feedback seriously in order to make sure the class gets the instruction they need. One of the best professors I've ever had!

When the class gave feedback on his teaching style the prof adapted and improved happily. His exams in the class had very similar questions to the practice questions he provides. Although he doesn't post answers, he is available to discuss answers. He also boosts the grades of midterms significantly.

One of the best professors I've ever had! His content is tricky but he presents it in an effective manner and is super easy to reach outside of class through email or office hours. Exams are tough as they are mainly long/short answer and apply lots of thinking but they reflect exactly what is in the lectures.

Pierre cares about his students. Even though the course material is difficult, he will adapt his teaching and take feedback seriously in order to make sure the class gets the instruction they need. Don't be afraid to ask questions in or outside of class because Pierre will make sure you get it!
